# Post-Change Model Audit (Dan standing preference)

After **every substantive code or config change** in this session, perform a **brief model audit** before reporting done. Dan wants confidence the cheapest capable model was used — and verification when a higher tier was warranted.

## Default worker

**Composer 2.5 Fast** implements all T0/T1/T2 work inline. Do not escalate for routine UI, service logic, or multi-file features unless a trigger below applies.

## Security gate timing

Run the Sonnet 4.6 security gate **before pushing** — not after commit. If Sonnet returns HIGH risk, fix before `git push origin main`. **Merged on main:** use commit-range diff (`git diff <commit>^..<commit>`); Sonnet/security-review subagent required before claiming PASS (detail: LIBRARIAN_LESSONS § process-agents #10).

## When to audit with a higher model (Sonnet 4.6 via Task subagent)

Run a short review **only if** the change (before push) touched any of:

| Trigger | Review focus |
|---------|----------------|
| `backend-write-critical` (Firestore rules, CF write paths, schema migrations) | Security, authz, data integrity |
| Auth / route guards / Firestore read paths on protected routes | Leaks, bypass, wrong actorType |
| Genuinely ambiguous high-stakes decision already implemented | Correctness vs intent |
| Composer uncertainty or failed first fix on T2+ work | Root cause + fix quality |

**Opus 4.6** — locked fallback only if Sonnet flags HIGH risk Composer cannot resolve.

## When Composer 2.5 alone is sufficient (no Sonnet pass)

- T0: `ui-component`, `css-restyle`, `docs-update`
- T1: `multi-file-feature`, `type-refactor`, `service-logic` **without** rules/auth changes
- T2: same as T1 when no auth/Firestore-read escalation trigger fired
- Pure Q&A, typos, read-only investigation
- Parallel read-only scouts (no Sonnet audit required)

## Audit output (mandatory in assistant reply)

Complete the **ship loop** (`ship-loop.mdc`) before declaring done for **code or config changes** — commit, push, and deploy must succeed (or deploy failure reported clearly). Read-only audits and rules/docs-only work: commit + push when applicable; no gh-pages deploy unless the bundle changed.

### Low-risk exemption (no full table)

For read-only audits, docs-only updates, rules-only updates, and other T0 non-product work, the final report does **not** need the full model audit table unless model choice or escalation was material. A short line is enough — e.g. `Model routing: T0 docs/rules; no escalation`.

End substantive **code/config** work with a compact block:

```
### Model audit
| Change | Archetype | Tier | Worker | Scouts parallel? | Escalation review? | Verdict |
|--------|-----------|------|--------|-------------------|-------------------|---------|
| … | … | … | Composer 2.5 | Yes / No / N/A | No / Sonnet → PASS | OK / note |
```

- **Verdict OK** — tier and worker matched the work; no review needed.
- **Verdict note** — Sonnet (or self) found an issue; fix or document before done.
- If escalation review was required but not run, **do not declare done** — run it first.

## Session log (optional)

When agent-ops outcome logging applies, include tier + whether audit escalated in the `note` field.
